@node "Welcome" "Welcome to Amiga Information Online"
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                          Editorial By Chris Seward
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

 Welcome back to Amiga Information Online, the source of great Amiga
things to come. This month has been some what hectic with alot of things
going on. Firstly this issue was supposed to come out with the new super
GUI, specially programmed for AIO with WB friendly window and also
AHI support etc. Unfortunally there where some minor hitchs near the
deadline and it wasn't possible to bring you the GUI. It will be out
for next issue no doubt about that.

 This issue we have a host of great things in store. A full review of
Fortresses new racer game, MAX Rally is reviewed aswell as some
interesting articles and other bits and bobs. Recently AIO got some
good press in Amiga Format which was a nice supprise, you can read the
full review of it this issue in the articles section or in AF Dec 1998
pd.select section.

 One of the best things about issue 18 is we have 5... yes 5 competitions
for Christmas. Some great things are to be won and its all the latest
and newest goodies. Check out the competition section from the main
menu.

 Well thats all I have to say in this cold month of November, don't
forget to check out issue 19 which comes out 6 days before Christmas
on the 19th December. Will we see any great releases around Christmas
like we did with Doom last year? who knows.

