@node "gr2" "Bang'Em"

@{fg shine} Bang'Em@{fg text}

 Bang'Em is yet another workbench game, yes we've reviewed tons of
them and you've probably played millions before. The ideas of WB games
seem to be running out fast as there isn't alot you can do in a WB
screen. Anyway onto Bang'Em...

 Bang'Em is made by the author of TVAP (The Very Annoying Program)
which i'm sure I reviewed a few issues back. The main plot around
Bang'Em is to hit the little faces or circles that appear, you all
should know the games you get at fairs or in arcades where you have
a hammer and have to hit the little monsters that pop up before they
go down. Bang'Em is exactly the same but with-out the hammer of course,
otherwise you'd damage your amiga no doubt. 

 It is played on a 10*8 board split into squares, you have a set time
limit and the faces/circles pop up and down and you have to click on
them. As soon as you have clicked on them they jump to another
position and you gain some points, if you don't hit a face before it
jumps them you'll loose points, you will also loose points if you
miss the face and hit an empty square.

 The graphics aren't anything pretty but what really can you expect
from a WB game? there isn't any sound apart from the clicking of your
mouse button. The playability is ok and the lastability is good if
you do boring tasks on your computer all day.

 The game is novel and will probably be good if your constantly sitting
at your computer doing work or downloading, it is a good stress toy
although you may get angry when you start loosing points for missing
faces and that'll lead to launching your computer across the room but
if you need a workbench game this is worth a look.

