@node "gr6" "WiZiO"

@{fg shine} WiZiO@{fg text}

 This is what the author discribes as a platform romp where you collect
coins, stars and special spells in a full screen scrolling world. Rather
like the Nintendo Classic Mario! But Mario is getting on now, he's even
in  3D, but what about his clones? 2D I'm afraid.

 Apon loading, you get a horribly pixelized screen, it looks like a part
of the in-game graphics has been enlarged, with a horrible output.

 Press FIRE, and after a while the ugly title screen fades to black, and
the scrolling world appears. The graphics are simple, but effective,
they serve their perpose well, they are not too fancy, and not too
dull.

 The gameplay is superb, this simple platformer is quality P.D, it's no
wonder it won the AF Reader Games a while back! One key to the brilliant
gameplay could be the dungeons, just look for a door and use any keys
you have picked up to open the door to be able to collect loads of
bonus', and when the door is open you can go in as many times as you
want, but you don't get any extra bonus'.

 Its hard to explain the quality of gameplay here, its too simple, but
its good. I surpose its one of those addictive games which have a real
simple idea behind them. Although, this is not an original game, its one
of the best P.D versions I've seen, of this type for a while.

 The trouble is, when you die, the enemies in the screen around you
disappear, but if you go away and come back, they come back as well!
Little bug there?

 I think what makes the game so addicive and playable, is the fact that
it is hard, after a few atempts it may be easy to get to level 2, but
after that it gets difficult, and you keep falling off the screen and
having to do level 1 again, which, after a while gets a bit tedious!

 I really like this one, call me sad, but I think its simplistic game
play makes it really good, but with 4 levels, and the authors lack of
support it may not become VERY good.

